@startuml metacloud
!include ../../../../../../tooling/styles/plantuml/structural/deployment-diagram-style.iuml

title Metacloud Architecture\nA centralized control layer abstracts cross-cloud management, operations, security, and governance

skinparam cloud {
  BackgroundColor #F4ECF7
  BorderColor #6C3483
}

actor "Cloud Resource\nAdministrators" as cra

package "Centralized Control Layer\n(meta layer)" as meta {
  component "Management" as mgmt
  component "Operations" as ops
  component "Security" as sec
  component "Governance" as gov
}

cloud "Cloud A" as cA
cloud "Cloud B" as cB
cloud "Cloud C" as cC

cra -down-> meta : single administration\naccess point

meta -down-> cA
meta -down-> cB
meta -down-> cC

note right of meta
  Meta layer can be hosted in:
  - a specific cloud,
  - distributed across clouds,
  - or on premises.
end note

note left of meta
  Best established before adopting
  multicloud, so the centralized
  administration layer is in place
  from the start.
  Improves agility and responsiveness
  to business change.
end note

@enduml
